abstract: Several thousand supporters of former Haitian President Jean-Bertrand Aristide fill the streets of Port-au-Prince, the capital, on the eighth anniversary of his ouster; turnout indicates mounting political strife between President Michel Martelly and his critics as the country continues to struggle to rebuild from the massive earthquake in 2010.
